President Biden and Chancellor Scholz had a phone call to discuss the ongoing war between Russia and Ukraine. They both expressed their support for Ukraine's sovereignty and independence and reaffirmed their solidarity with the Ukrainian people. The United States plans to supply Ukraine with Bradley Infantry Fighting Vehicles, while Germany will provide Marder Infantry Fighting Vehicles. Both countries also intend to train Ukrainian forces on these systems. Additionally, in response to Russia's attacks on Ukraine's critical infrastructure, the United States and Germany will supply Ukraine with Patriot air defense missile batteries. President Biden and Chancellor Scholz appreciated the military support provided by other Allies and partners to Ukraine and welcomed additional donations of air defense systems and combat vehicles.